http://www.irishmirror.ie/sport/soccer/soccer-news/bohemians-boss-keith-long-admits-10420566}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, Akinade was issued a [[deportation]] order. His application to have the deportation stopped was rejected in the [[High Court (Ireland)|High Court]] in May 2019.<ref name=\"ishmaildeportation\">{{cite web |title=Z.A. -v- The Minister for Justice and Equality |url=http://www.courts.ie/Judgments.nsf/768d83be24938e1180256ef30048ca51/742f5c6a7cadd0dd80258412004e5c63?OpenDocument |website=courts.ie |accessdate=27 June 2019}}</ref> He returned to Nigeria voluntarily in June.<ref name=\"akinadeexit\">{{cite news |last1=Ward |first1=Johnny |title=Blow for Waterford as Akinade makes swift exit |url=https://www.rte.ie/sport/soccer/2019/0624/1057321-blow-for-waterford-as-akinade-makes-swift-exit/ |accessdate=27 June 2019 |work=RT\u00c9 News |date=25 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"independentfaildeportation\">{{cite news |last1=Brady |first1=Tom |title=Soccer star deported from Ireland joins Vietnamese outfit on lucrative deal |url=https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/courts/soccer-star-deported-from-ireland-joins-vietnamese-outfit-on-lucrative-deal-38261275.html |accessdate=28 June 2019 |work=Irish Independent |date=28 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Bohemians'''\n*[[Leinster Senior Cup (association football)|Lenister Senior Cup]]: [[2015\u201316 Leinster Senior Cup|2015\u201316]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway|252497}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Akinade, Ismahil}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Ibadan]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Nigerian footballers]]\n[[Category:League of Ireland players]]\n[[Category:Bray Wanderers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:St Patrick's Athletic F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bohemian F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Waterford F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Nigerian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Nigerian expatriate sportspeople in Ireland]]\n[[Category:Expatriate association footballers in the Republic of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Leinster Senior League (association football) players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Nigerian footaballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name              = Ismahil Akinade\n| image             =\n| caption           =\n| fullname          = Ismahil Akinade\n| birth_date        = {{birth date and age|1994|2|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[Ibadan]], Nigeria\n| currentclub       = [[Free agent]]\n| clubnumber        = \n| height            = 1.90 m\n| position          = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1       = 2012 | youthclubs1 = [[St Patrick's Athletic F.C.|St Patrick's Athletic]]\n| years1 = 2012\u20132014 | clubs1 = [[Bray Wanderers A.F.C.|Bray Wanderers]]             | caps1 = 64 | goals1 = 8\n| years2 = 2015\u20132017 | clubs2 = [[Bohemian F.C.|Bohemians]]                          | caps2 = 52 | goals2 = 19\n| years3 = 2018\u20132019 | clubs3 = [[Waterford F.C.|Waterford]]                         | caps3 = 49 | goals3 = 8\n| years4 = 2019      | clubs4 = [[H\u1ed3 Ch\u00ed Minh City F.C.|H\u1ed3 Ch\u00ed Minh City]]           | caps4 = 10 | goals4 = 4\n| pcupdate          = 08:28, 24 February 2020 (UTC)\n| ntupdate          =\n}}\n\n'''Ismahil Akinade''' (born 11 February 1994) is a Nigerian-born<ref name=\"goal\">{{cite web|title=Nigerian striker Ismahil Akinade extends stay at Irish club Bohemians|url=http://www.goal.com/en-ng/news/4110/nigerians-abroad/2015/10/31/16851032/nigerian-striker-ismahil-akinade-extends-stay-at-irish-club|website=Goal|accessdate=29 May 2016|date=31 October 2015}}</ref> [[Association football|footballer]] who most recently played as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[H\u1ed3 Ch\u00ed Minh City F.C.|H\u1ed3 Ch\u00ed Minh City]]\n\n==Career==\n===Bray Wanderers===\nAkinade started his career at [[St Patrick's Athletic F.C.|St Patrick's Athletic]] Under 19's (making the bench for the first team once as an unused substitute) before moving on to [[Bray Wanderers F.C.|Bray Wanderers]] where he was a huge hit with fans and won the club's Young Player of the Year award for the [[2013 League of Ireland|2013 season]]. Akinade parted ways with Bray at the end of the [[2014 League of Ireland|2014 season]] after he played a huge part in guaranteeing the ''Seagulls''' safety in the [[League of Ireland Premier Division|Premier Division]].\n\n===Bohemians===\nMidway through the [[2015 League of Ireland]] season, Akinade signed for [[Bohemian F.C.|Bohemians]], making his debut in a 2\u20131 win away to [[Dundalk F.C.|Dundalk]] on 6 June, setting up the first goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.extratime.ie/articles/14411/league-report-dundalk-1---2-bohemians/|title=League Report: Dundalk 1 - 2 Bohemians - ExtraTime.ie|publisher=|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref> Akinade was nominated for Young Player Of The Year<ref name=\"goal\"/> after scoring 10 goals in 18 matches in his first season with the club. In October 2015, he agreed to a new contract.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fitzmaurice|first1=Aidan|title=Akinade deal boosts Euro hopefuls Bohs|url=http://www.herald.ie/sport/akinade-deal-boosts-euro-hopefuls-bohs-34152876.html|accessdate=29 May 2016|work=[[The Herald (Ireland)]]|date=30 October 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"goal\"/> Akinade went on to score 5 goals in 18 appearances for the 2016 season and in the 2017 season injury ruled him out for the first half of the season, when he returned he scored memorable goals against fierce rivals [[Shamrock Rovers F.C.|Shamrock Rovers]] in a 2\u20131 win in Tallaght<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sseairtricityleague.ie/news/report-shamrock-rovers-12-bohemians/id-883|title=SSE Airtricity League|website=sseairtricityleague.ie|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref> and the winner against [[Dundalk F.C.|Dundalk]] in Oriel Park.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.extratime.ie/articles/19930/league-report-dundalk-0---1-bohemians/|title=League Report: Dundalk 0 - 1 Bohemians - ExtraTime.ie|publisher=|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Waterford===\nAkinade left Bohs to sign for [[Waterford F.C.|Waterford]] for the 2018 [[League of Ireland Premier Division]] season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.waterfordfc.ie/blues-swoop-premier-division-duo/|title=Blues Swoop for Premier Division Duo - Waterford FC|date=17 November 2017|publisher=|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref> Akinade made his debut in a 2\u20131 win against [[Derry City F.C.|Derry City]] on 17 February 2018.<ref>http://www.waterfordfc.ie/report-waterford-fc-2-derry-city-1-sse-airtricity-league/</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=REPORT: Waterford FC 2 Derry City 1 \u2013 SSE Airtricity League |url=http://www.waterfordfc.ie/report-waterford-fc-2-derry-city-1-sse-airtricity-league/ |website=Waterford FC |accessdate=25 June 2019}}</ref> He departed from the club by mutual agreement on 24 June 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dempsey |first1=Andrew |title=Ismahil Akinade departs Waterford by mutual agreement |url=http://www.extratime.ie/articles/23083/ismahil-akinade-departs-waterford-by-mutual-agreement/ |website=Extratime.ie |accessdate=25 June 2019 |date=24 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n===H\u1ed3 Ch\u00ed Minh City===\nOn 28 June 2019, [[V.League 1]] side [[H\u1ed3 Ch\u00ed Minh City F.C.|H\u1ed3 Ch\u00ed Minh City]] announced the signing of Akinade.<ref name=\"independentfaildeportation\"/> He made a scoring debut for the club that same day in a game against [[Th\u1ec3 C\u00f4ng F.C.|Viettel FC]] in the [[Vietnamese National Football Cup]].<ref>{{Citation|last=Ho Chi Minh City F.C|title=HCMC F.C {{!}} CLB TP. H\u1ed3 Ch\u00ed Minh b\u1ed5 sung ti\u1ec1n \u0111\u1ea1o Ismaheel Akinade|date=28 June 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B_CFOnhVRWM|access-date=28 June 2019}}</ref> He left at the end of the season following 5 goals in 11 games, with the club looking to replace him with former [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] striker [[David N'Gog]].<ref>https://www.rte.ie/sport/soccer/2019/1213/1098937-ho-chi-minh-could-replace-izzy-akinade-with-david-ngog/</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{Updated|24 February 2020}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://us.soccerway.com/players/ismahil-akinade/252497/|title=Republic of Ireland \u2013 I.Akinade|publisher=ie.soccerway.com|accessdate=17 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division||Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[St Patrick's Athletic F.C.|St Patrick's Athletic]]\n|[[2012 St Patrick's Athletic F.C. season|2012]]\n|[[League of Ireland Premier Division]]\n|0||0||0||0||0||0||0{{efn|Appearances in [[UEFA Europa League]]|name=statsUEL}}||0||0{{efn|Appearances in [[Leinster Senior Cup (association football)|Leinster Senior Cup]]|name=statsLSC}}||0||0||0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Bray Wanderers F.C.|Bray Wanderers]]\n|[[2012 League of Ireland Premier Division|2012]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|League of Ireland Premier Division\n|5||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0{{efn|Appearances in [[Leinster Senior Cup (association football)|Leinster Senior Cup]]|name=statsLSC}}||0||5||0\n|-\n|[[2013 League of Ireland Premier Division|2013]]\n|31||6||2||0||1||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||4{{efn|2 appearances in [[2013 League of Ireland Premier Division|League of Ireland Promotion/Relegation Playoff]], 2 appearances & 3 goals in [[Leinster Senior Cup (association football)|Leinster Senior Cup]]}}||3||38||10\n|-\n|[[2014 League of Ireland Premier Division|2014]]\n|28||2||0||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0{{efn|Appearances in [[Leinster Senior Cup (association football)|Leinster Senior Cup]]|name=statsLSC}}||0||30||2\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!63!!8!!2!!0!!3!!1!!colspan=2|\u2014!!4!